    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I work on Linux, I don't know how `pts` works on other plateforms.\n\nFor me this bug happens not only for `less`, but for all programs which need `pts` allocation.\nFor example, with `vim`, it is working by the magic `%edit`, but not with `!vim`.\n\nFor the magic, `vim` is launched by `subprocess.Popen`, and for the bang, from `pexpect.spawn`.\n\nA workaround can be:\n\n```\ndiff --git a/IPython/utils/_process_posix.py b/IPython/utils/_process_posix.py\nindex ac3a9a0..997ac9d 100644\n--- a/IPython/utils/_process_posix.py\n+++ b/IPython/utils/_process_posix.py\n@@ -155,6 +155,7 @@ def system(self, cmd):\n                 child = pexpect.spawnb(self.sh, args=['-c', cmd]) # Pexpect-U\n             else:\n                 child = pexpect.spawn(self.sh, args=['-c', cmd])  # Vanilla Pexpect\n+            child.interact()\n             flush = sys.stdout.flush\n             while True:\n                 # res is the index of the pattern that caused the match, so we\n```\n\nBut the problem is not solved, `vim` with `!vim` is still launched with new `pts` with wrong size, but with `interact()` method, the keystrokes are send to the good `pts`, and it partially works.\n"
  },
